Subject: [R-meta] 
 Interaction between a continuous variable and a 3-level
 categorical variable
In-Reply-To: <YT2PR01MB61100AA7F314336000BB368BB70F9@YT2PR01MB6110.CANPRD01.PROD.OUTLOOK.COM>
References: <YT2PR01MB61100AA7F314336000BB368BB70F9@YT2PR01MB6110.CANPRD01.PROD.OUTLOOK.COM>
Message-ID: <95bcc2488c4749e7b7c79830e6319f0d@UM-MAIL3213.unimaas.nl>

Hi Roger,

This should do it:

m2 <- rma.mv(angle ~ -1 + temp*recipe, V=0, random = list(~ 1|replicate, ~ 1|ID), data=cake, test="t")
summary(m2)
anova(m2, btt="temp:recipe")

sav <- robust(m2, cluster=cake$replicate)
sav
anova(sav, btt="temp:recipe")

Best,
Wolfgang

